    <h1>ABES Engineering College</h1>
    <h2>Department of ASH</h2>
    <h3>Course Curriculum - Web Designing (25VA151)</h3>
    <hr>

    <p><b>Course Title:</b> <i>Web Designing</i></p>
    <p><b>Faculty Name:</b> Ms. Deepti Deshmukh, Mr. Jitendra Kumar Chauhan, 
       Mr. Sanjeev Soni, Ms. Pranshi Verma, Ms. Monika, Mr. Rohit Pratap Singh</p>
    <p><u>Approved by:</u> AICTE, New Delhi &copy; 2025</p>

    <h3>Course Objectives:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>To understand the basics of HTML and CSS.</li>
        <li>To design a simple webpage structure.</li>
        <li>To implement various HTML elements like text, lists, and links.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Course Outcomes:</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Apply HTML tags for webpage design.</li>
        <li>Use formatting and list elements effectively.</li>
        <li>Develop well-structured webpages using semantic HTML.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Course Modules:</h3>
    <dl>
        <dt><b>Module 1:</b></dt>
        <dd>Introduction to HTML, Headings, Paragraphs, and Lists.</dd>
        <dt><b>Module 2:</b></dt>
        <dd>Working with Images, Links, and Tables.</dd>
        <dt><b>Module 3:</b></dt>
        <dd>Introduction to CSS and Layout Design.</dd>
    </dl>

    <h3>Example of Nested and Mixed Lists:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>HTML Basics
            <ol>
                <li>Tags and Elements</li>
                <li>Attributes</li>
            </ol>
        </li>
        <li>Formatting Text
            <ul>
                <li><b>Bold</b></li>
                <li><i>Italic</i></li>
                <li><u>Underline</u></li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Lists
            <ul>
                <li>Ordered List</li>
                <li>Unordered List</li>
                <li>Mixed List Example:
                    <ol>
                        <li>Definition List</li>
                        <li>Nested Lists</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <hr>
    <p><b>Note:</b> This webpage demonstrates the use of <i>text formatting</i>, 
       <u>lists</u>, and <b>special characters</b> like &copy;, &lt;, &gt;, and &amp;.</p>

